  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6602.79 sitting just below the massive +50.4B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to sell any push higher while providing support on dips toward the 6590 negative gamma pocket. The PIN regime with 114.4B total GEX creates a tight trading range between 6590-6610, where the flip strike at 6610 acts as the upper bound for mean reversion dynamics. The gex_surge event and extreme 5-minute GEX change of 589% indicates heavy options flow is pinning price action around these critical levels.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to bounce between 6590 and 6610 with dealers fighting moves outside this range.",
